  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "/oSJG45ZOJB/A+kBBQYz//TDTeA=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:34.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# error classes in reducers are auto-imported by name reference\n\nIn reducer code, you reference error classes by name without importing them:\n\n```typescript\n// \u2705 Just reference the error \u2014 auto-imported\nthrow new MissingIdError(\"ID is required\");\nthrow new EntryNotFoundError(\"Entry not found\");\n\n// \u274c Don't manually import\nimport { MissingIdError } from \"../../gen/module-name/error.js\";\nthrow new MissingIdError(\"ID is required\");\n\n// \u274c Don't use nested access patterns\nthrow new errors.ModuleName.MissingIdError(\"message\");\n```\n\nThe code generator scans reducer code for error class references and adds the appropriate imports automatically. Manually importing creates duplicate imports or path mismatches.\n\nSince [[error names must end with Error and use PascalCase]], the generator matches on the PascalCase class name ending in \"Error\".\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[reducer patterns]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:34.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:34.000Z"
    }
  },
